typealias <caret>TypeAliasG<X> = List<X>
//INFO: <div class='definition'><pre><span style="color:#000080;font-weight:bold;">public</span> <span style="color:#000080;font-weight:bold;">typealias</span> <span style="color:#000000;">TypeAliasG</span><span style="">&lt;</span><span style="color:#20999d;">X</span><span style="">&gt;</span> = <span style="color:#000000;"><a href="psi_element://kotlin.collections.List">List</a></span><span style="">&lt;</span><span style="color:#20999d;"><a href="psi_element://TypeAliasG.X">X</a></span><span style="">&gt;</span></pre></div><div class='bottom'><icon src="KotlinBaseResourcesIcons.Kotlin_file"/>&nbsp;TypeAliasG.kt<br/></div><div class='definition'><pre><span style="color:#000080;font-weight:bold;">public</span> <span style="color:#000080;font-weight:bold;">interface</span> <span style="color:#000000;">List</span><span style="">&lt;</span><span style="color:#000080;font-weight:bold;">out</span> <span style="color:#20999d;">E</span><span style="">&gt;</span> : <span style="color:#000000;"><a href="psi_element://kotlin.collections.Collection">Collection</a></span><span style="">&lt;</span><span style="color:#20999d;"><a href="psi_element://kotlin.collections.List.E">E</a></span><span style="">&gt;</span></pre></div><div class='content'><p style='margin-top:0;padding-top:0;'>A generic ordered collection of elements. The interface allows iterating over contained elements, accessing elements by index, checking if a list contains some elements, and searching indices for particular values. Complex operations are built upon this functionality and provided in form of <a href="psi_element://kotlin.collections"><code><span style="color:#000000;">kotlin</span><span style="">.</span><span style="color:#4585be;">collections</span></code></a> extension functions.</p>
//INFO: <p>Functions in this interface support only read-only access to the list; read/write access is supported through the <a href="psi_element://MutableList"><code><span style="color:#0000ff;">MutableList</span></code></a> interface.</p>
//INFO: <p>In addition to a regular iteration, it is possible to obtain <a href="psi_element://ListIterator"><code><span style="color:#0000ff;">ListIterator</span></code></a> using <a href="psi_element://listIterator"><code><span style="color:#0000ff;">listIterator</span></code></a> that provides bidirectional iteration facilities, and allows accessing elements' indices in addition to their values.</p>
//INFO: <p>It is possible to get a view over a continuous span of elements using <a href="psi_element://subList"><code><span style="color:#0000ff;">subList</span></code></a>.</p>
//INFO: <p>Unlike <a href="psi_element://Set"><code><span style="color:#0000ff;">Set</span></code></a>, lists can contain duplicate elements.</p>
//INFO: <p>Unlike <a href="psi_element://Collection"><code><span style="color:#0000ff;">Collection</span></code></a> implementations, <a href="psi_element://List"><code><span style="color:#0000ff;">List</span></code></a> implementations must override <a href="psi_element://Any.toString"><code><span style="color:#000000;">Any</span><span style="">.</span><span style="color:#0000ff;">toString</span></code></a>, <a href="psi_element://Any.equals"><code><span style="color:#000000;">Any</span><span style="">.</span><span style="color:#0000ff;">equals</span></code></a> and <a href="psi_element://Any.hashCode"><code><span style="color:#000000;">Any</span><span style="">.</span><span style="color:#0000ff;">hashCode</span></code></a> functions and provide implementations such that:</p>
//INFO:  <ul><li><p><a href="psi_element://List.toString"><code><span style="color:#000000;">List</span><span style="">.</span><span style="color:#0000ff;">toString</span></code></a> should return a string containing string representation of contained elements in exact same order these elements are stored within the list.</p>
//INFO: </li> <li><p><a href="psi_element://List.equals"><code><span style="color:#000000;">List</span><span style="">.</span><span style="color:#0000ff;">equals</span></code></a> should consider two lists equal if and only if they contain the same number of elements and each element in one list is equal to an element in another list at the same index.</p>
//INFO: </li> <li><p><a href="psi_element://List.hashCode"><code><span style="color:#000000;">List</span><span style="">.</span><span style="color:#0000ff;">hashCode</span></code></a> should be computed as a combination of elements' hash codes using the following algorithm:</p>
//INFO: </li></ul>
//INFO: <pre><code><span style="color:#000080;font-weight:bold;">var&#32;</span><span style="">hashCode:&#32;Int&#32;=&#32;</span><span style="color:#0000ff;">1<br></span><span style="color:#000080;font-weight:bold;">for&#32;</span><span style="">(element&#32;</span><span style="color:#000080;font-weight:bold;">in&#32;this</span><span style="">)&#32;hashCode&#32;=&#32;hashCode&#32;*&#32;</span><span style="color:#0000ff;">31&#32;</span><span style="">+&#32;element?.hashCode()&#32;?:&#32;</span><span style="color:#0000ff;">0</span></code></pre><p>By convention, <a href="psi_element://List"><code><span style="color:#0000ff;">List</span></code></a> implementations are usually also implement <a href="psi_element://java.io.Serializable"><code><span style="color:#000000;">java</span><span style="">.</span><span style="color:#000000;">io</span><span style="">.</span><span style="color:#0000ff;">Serializable</span></code></a>.</p></div><table class='sections'><tr><td valign='top' class='section'><p>Type parameters:</td><td valign='top'><p><code><a href="psi_element://E"><code><span style="color:#20999d;">E</span></code></a></code> - the type of elements contained in the list. The list is covariant in its element type.</td></table><div class='bottom'><icon src="AllIcons.Nodes.Package"/>&nbsp;<a href="psi_element://kotlin.collections"><code><span style="color:#000000;">kotlin.collections</span></code></a><br/><icon src="KotlinBaseResourcesIcons.Kotlin_file"/>&nbsp;Collections.kt<br/></div>
